## âœ¨ Features

### ğŸ¤– Specialized AI Agents

> **Each agent is purpose-built with 10-36 specialized tools and expert system prompts**

<details open>
<summary><h4>â­ Quill - Equity Research Analyst</h4></summary>

**Deep fundamental analysis & investment thesis building**

**Core Capabilities**:
- ğŸ“Š **Valuation Models**: DCF, comparable company analysis, P/E/P/B/P/S ratios
- ğŸ“ˆ **Financial Analysis**: 5-year trends (revenue, margins, ROIC, FCF, debt ratios)
- ğŸ’° **Earnings Tracking**: Historical earnings, analyst estimates, surprise analysis
- ğŸ¯ **Analyst Coverage**: Consensus ratings, price targets, upgrades/downgrades
- ğŸ¢ **Ownership Tracking**: Institutional holders, insider transactions (Form 4)
- ğŸ“‹ **SEC Filings**: 10-K, 10-Q, 8-K material events, XBRL structured data
- ğŸ’µ **Dividends**: Yield, payout ratios, dividend history, sustainability
- ğŸ“° **News Validation**: Company-specific news with sentiment analysis

**Tools**: 36 specialized tools across Yahoo Finance, SEC EDGAR, Tiingo, Finnhub, NewsAPI

**Command**: `/quill`

**Example Query**:
> "Analyze AAPL with focus on recent earnings trends, institutional ownership, and material events from 8-K filings"

</details>

<details>
<summary><h4>ğŸ“Š Earnings Whisperer - Earnings Specialist</h4></summary>

**Earnings surprise analysis & post-earnings drift detection**

**Core Capabilities**:
- ğŸ¯ **Historical Analysis**: 4-8 quarter earnings surprise tracking
- ğŸ“ˆ **Drift Detection**: 1-3 day post-earnings momentum patterns
- ğŸ”„ **Analyst Revisions**: Estimate changes and rating updates post-earnings
- âœ… **Quality Assessment**: Revenue vs. EPS beats, non-recurring items
- ğŸ“… **Calendar Monitoring**: Upcoming earnings with probability scoring
- ğŸ† **Pattern Recognition**: Consistent beaters, accelerating beats, quality issues
- ğŸ’¹ **Trading Signals**: BUY (drift play), HOLD (wait), SELL (negative momentum)

**Tools**: 14 specialized tools across Yahoo Finance, SEC, Finnhub

**Command**: `/earnings`

**Example Query**:
> "Analyze NVDA earnings history - is there a post-earnings drift opportunity?"

</details>

<details>
<summary><h4>ğŸ” Screen Forge - Equity Screener</h4></summary>

**Systematic stock discovery & idea generation**

**Core Capabilities**:
- ğŸ“ **Multi-Factor Screening**: Value, growth, quality, momentum factors
- ğŸ¯ **Systematic Discovery**: Weekly watchlist generation with factor-based ranking
- ğŸ“ˆ **Earnings Momentum**: Consistent earnings beat screening
- â¬†ï¸ **Analyst Activity**: Upgrade/downgrade filtering
- ğŸ’¬ **Sentiment Validation**: News and social sentiment checks
- ğŸ”— **Integration**: Seamless handoff to Quill for deep-dive analysis

**Tools**: 15 specialized tools across Yahoo Finance, Finnhub, Alpha Vantage

**Command**: `/screen`

**Example Query**:
> "Screen for stocks with consistent earnings beats over last 3 quarters and analyst upgrades"

</details>

<details>
<summary><h4>ğŸŒ Macro Lens - Market Strategist</h4></summary>

**Top-down macro analysis & regime identification**

**Core Capabilities**:
- ğŸ”„ **Economic Cycles**: 4-phase regime analysis (early/mid/late expansion, recession)
- ğŸ“ˆ **Yield Curve**: Interpretation and recession signal detection (inversions)
- ğŸ­ **Sector Allocation**: Macro-driven sector positioning guidance
- ğŸ“Š **Factor Recommendations**: Value vs. growth, size, low-volatility tilts
- ğŸ“‰ **Macro Tracking**: Inflation, GDP growth, employment, Fed policy
- ğŸ“Š **Market Indices**: S&P 500, Nasdaq, VIX for regime correlation
- ğŸ’¹ **Interest Rates**: Fed funds, treasury rates, spreads

**Tools**: 13 specialized tools across FRED, U.S. Treasury, Yahoo Finance, NewsAPI

**Command**: `/macro`

**Example Query**:
> "What's the current macro regime and which sectors should I overweight?"

</details>

<details>
<summary><h4>ğŸ—ºï¸ Atlas - Investment Strategist</h4></summary>

**Strategic asset allocation & portfolio construction**

**Core Capabilities**:
- ğŸ“‹ **IPS Development**: Investment Policy Statement creation
- ğŸ¯ **Asset Allocation**: Strategic allocation frameworks (stocks/bonds/alternatives)
- ğŸ“Š **Risk Profiling**: Conservative/Moderate/Aggressive tolerance assessment
- ğŸ”„ **Tactical Tilts**: Macro-driven portfolio adjustments
- âš–ï¸ **Rebalancing**: Threshold-based, calendar-based, tax-aware strategies
- ğŸ—ï¸ **Construction**: Portfolio building with constraint optimization

**Tools**: 12 specialized tools across all data sources

**Command**: `/atlas`

**Example Query**:
> "Create an IPS for moderate risk tolerance with $100k portfolio"

</details>

<details>
<summary><h4>ğŸ“ Portfolio & Research (Legacy)</h4></summary>

